From author's meeting 2025-05-13:

Idea for inventing a new identifier type; borrowing an idea from either CRL-DP, and/or ACME

```
{
  dn: "cn=CertA",
  SPKI: <>,
  extns:
    DCD: {
      dcd_id: 1a2b3c4d
      OR
      dcd_id: "http://ca.cacorp.com/certs/1a2b3c4d"
    }

}


{
  dn: "cn=CertB",
  SPKI: <>,
  extns:
    DCD: {
      dcd_url: "http://ca.cacorp.com/certs/1a2b3c4d"
    }

}
```

RFC 5697 uses this structure for issuerSerial and includes a full Hash of the certificate.

SCVPCertID ::= SEQUENCE {
       certHash        OCTET STRING,
       issuerSerial    SCVPIssuerSerial,
       hashAlgorithm   AlgorithmIdentifier DEFAULT { algorithm sha-1 } }

SCVPIssuerSerial ::= SEQUENCE {
        issuer         GeneralNames,
        serialNumber   CertificateSerialNumber
   }


So we could replace our optional CertHash:

CertHash ::= SEQUENCE {
   value OCTET STRING,
   hashAlgorithm AlgorithmIdentifier DEFAULT {algorithm sha-256}
}

With SCVPCertID
  -  Which would also require the issuer and Serial as well as the Hash as optional values

